║  Location: Bridge - Datalink Terminal                                 ║
╚═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╝

┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│  ARIA BACKUP: The ship's status monitoring system stores data in       │
│  JSON format. I need you to extract critical readings using the        │
│  datalink tools: curl and jq.                                          │
│                                                                        │
│  curl can fetch data from local files using the file:// protocol.      │
│  jq is a powerful JSON processor - think of it as "grep for JSON".     │
│                                                                        │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘

═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

MISSION BRIEFING:

Two JSON data files contain ship status information:
  • ship_status.json   - Core system readings
  • sensor_readings.json - Environmental sensor data

Extract THREE critical values and write them to 'status_report.txt':
  1. The reactor temperature (from ship_status.json)
  2. The shield percentage (from ship_status.json)
  3. The oxygen level (from sensor_readings.json)

FORMAT for status_report.txt (one value per line):
  <reactor_temp>
  <shield_percent>
  <oxygen_level>

Example (with made-up values):
  850
  92
  21.5

═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

CURL BASICS:

  curl file://$(pwd)/ship_status.json    - Fetch local file via curl
  curl -s ...                            - Silent mode (no progress bar)

JQ BASICS:

  jq '.'                    - Pretty print entire JSON
  jq '.field'               - Extract a top-level field
  jq '.parent.child'        - Extract nested field
  jq -r '.field'            - Raw output (no quotes)

EXAMPLE PIPELINE:

  curl -s file://$(pwd)/data.json | jq -r '.temperature'

═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

OBJECTIVES:

1. Examine the JSON files to understand their structure
2. Use curl and jq to extract the three values
3. Write the values to status_report.txt (one per line, in order)
4. Run ./verify to check your work

═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

NOTE: This mission requires 'jq' to be installed. If you don't have it:
  macOS:  brew install jq
  Linux:  sudo apt install jq  (or: sudo yum install jq)

═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
